# Quicklyway Design System (Single Rule)

When adding or editing UI (landing page, dashboard, admin, components):

## Border radius
- **Pills**: Use `rounded-full` for **buttons** and **badges** only.
- **Everything else**: Use `rounded-lg` for inputs, textareas, cards, dropdowns, tables, tabs, tooltip, toggle, skeleton, menubar. Do not use `rounded-md` or `rounded-xl` for these — stick to `rounded-lg`.

## Typography
Use these classes for headings and text so font size and weight stay consistent:
- **H1**: `className="heading-1"` or `text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight`
- **H2**: `className="heading-2"` or `text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight`
- **H3**: `className="heading-3"` or `text-xl font-medium`
- **H4**: `className="heading-4"` or `text-lg font-medium`
- **H5**: `className="heading-5"` or `text-base font-medium`
- **H6**: `className="heading-6"` or `text-sm font-medium`
- **Body**: `text-base`
- **Small**: `text-sm`
- **Caption**: `className="caption"` or `text-xs text-muted-foreground`

## Colors
Use only design tokens: `primary`, `primary-foreground`, `secondary`, `muted`, `muted-foreground`, `accent`, `destructive`, `border`, `background`, `foreground`, `card`, `popover`. No ad-hoc hex/rgb.

